headline: FedEx doubles down on premium e-commerce, delivery surcharges
summary: When it comes to e-commerce delivery, FedEx only wants longer-haul, heavy and high-value parcels because operating as a local courier for small packages isn’t profitable. The post FedEx doubles down on premium e-commerce, delivery surcharges appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: New Owner of 21-Year-Old PostalAnnex in Eagle, Idaho Brings New Ideas to Expand Shipping, Office Services, and the Future of the Business
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., a leading franchisor in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is pleased to announce the successful transfer of ownership of an existing PostalAnnex location in Eagle, ID to new owner, Don Holladay. This transition to new ownership ensures that the community will benefit from the essential shipping and office services provided by this PostalAnnex location for the last 21 years.

headline: How Recent Developments Are Reframing The FedEx (FDX) Investment Story Through 2029
summary: The latest update to our FedEx view lifts fair value from US$306.54 to US$370.46 per share, supported by a slightly lower 8.67% discount rate and a modest increase in the assumed 4.26% annual revenue growth rate. These adjustments reflect how recent Investor Day messaging and street research are reshaping expectations around FedEx’s long term plan and the risks tied to it.
